<br>
My name is Mike, I'm 19 years old, and I have very bad luck with relationships it seems hehe.  I don't think I'm a bad looking kid, I'm 6'1&quot;, 185 pounds, deep blue eyes, dusty blond hair, a very nice tan, and I think I'm in fairly good physical shape (note: I look 16, not sure why, I just do).  Now then, as far as personality goes, I'm a very deep logical thinker, I always think things through before acting, I always look at the consequences before doing, etc, as a result, I have never touched drugs, very rairly drink (I drink some, but I never drive after drinking), and so on.  I treat women with the utmost respect, I am very nice to them and very much a gentleman, when I go out with a girl, I ALWAYS pay, and if they offer, I say that I appreciate the offer, but I wouldn't be much of a gentleman if I let them pay.<br>
<br>
I don't really go out of my way to meet women, I figure that when I meet the right one, I'll know it and it won't be at a bar or someplace like that (no offence to bar women, but there's no way I could spend my life with the kinda girls you meet at most bars), I don't even go to bars or most &quot;teenage hang out points&quot; because being around drugs and such just isn't my style.  I usually meet people by like a friend introducing me to a friend, or something like that, and that's how I meet girls for the most part.  I'll often hang out with friends and stuff, see a cute girl, flirt a little, but never ask for her number or anything, because it's just not &quot;my style&quot; to hit on every girl or ask every girl out.. Basically I'm a &quot;one woman man.&quot;<br>
<br>
Now then, as far as relationships go, it seems as though I'll find out from someone that a girl likes me and wants me to ask her out or something, so I will, and this is how my last girlfriend went:  She was hanging out with a group of my friends one time when I wasn't there, and like no one talked to her, so she was complaining to my buddy Zak that no one talked to her, so he gave her my AIM screen name and said &quot;this guy will talk to ya&quot; and told her about me, we talked and stuff and she told him she hopes I ask her out, he told me, so I decided to take a chance and basically go on a &quot;blind date.&quot;  We meet, she's about 4'11&quot; and pretty damn cute, so we go out to a movie and dinner, then come back to my place and hang out... well there's like nothing to talk about so we end up making out for a while then I take her home.. really good first date I figure.  I could tell she was REALLY into me, and I really liked her but I didn't know anything about her, but I figured I'd learn more about her and give it a shot.. By the way, she had just turned 17 like 2 days before.<br>
<br>
Ok, I take her home and tell her I had a good time and such, she says she had a REALLY good time, kisses me good night, and asked me if I'd mind getting on AIM when I get home so we can talk some more.. I say ok, and get online when I get home.. we didn't talk that much but we kinda &quot;talked through my friend&quot; because there are awkward questions you don't wanna directly ask the other person.  Anyway, I said I was very scared of getting hurt again (I had just spent 2 months of the worst depression of my life trying to get over my last girlfriend), and she was saying how much she liked me and felt so right about me, etc.  Well I finally told my friend that I'm gunna take a chance with her, she seems like a good enough / nice enough girl, so the next day we went out again and became official.  A day or 2 later we were talking about sex, and I found out she's a virgin.. good news to me, because my biggest fear was that she would be easy.  I find out a number of other things about her, and realize she's pretty much what I wanted in a girlfriend, so I tell her that I really like her back and I'm not afraid of moving too fast anymore, she's really happy and we basically turn into a fairly serious relationship, very fast.<br>
<br>
All's well for several days and we're having a lot of fun together, I'm really starting to get into her but there's still no love of course, everything seems well, she keeps telling me how much she likes me and feels so right, then all at once, without warning, she breaks up with me.. This is line I get &quot;I'm sorry, I just don't feel it anymore.. You seem like a REALLY nice guy and any girl would be lucky to be with you, but I just don't like you as more than a friend anymore.. can we start over as just friends?  It's nothing you did, it's nothing you said, you're a great guy.. it's not you it's me.&quot;<br>
<br>
Ok, this seemingly is the story of my life.. I have NO trouble meeting women, talking to women, getting them interested in me, being a good boyfriend, treating them right, etc.. but somehow I have a very hard time holding onto a serious relationship, it seems like shortly after it gets really serious, they suddenly don't like me anymore, yet they REALLY want a serious relationship with me days (or mere hours) before.. I always get &quot;you did nothing wrong, you're a great guy.. I just don't feel that way anymore.&quot;<br>
<br>
So, to all the women out there (or men who know an inordinate amount about women), is there something wrong with me?  Is it just that I happen to get weird women that have emotional issues or are really unstable?  Is it that I'm too nice?  What is it?  I've never had a fight with a girlfriend at all.. I play fought with em sometimes or had a discussion about something, but never even raised our voices at eachother.. is that the problem?  We got along too well that they got bored?  Or is there something wrong with me?  I need help! lol<br>
<br>
Anyway, I know this was long, and I apologizing, but I guess I just needed to vent <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .<br>
<br>
-Mike <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub12.ezboard.com/bxevserverboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=thedosiusdreamtwister>Thedosius Dreamtwister</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://members.rogers.com/shadowgovernment01/thedhead.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered Member</span><br>  Posts: 136<br> <font color=#330000>(6/27/03 2:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub228.ezboard.com/fxevserverboardsfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=815.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Women... Are They Weird or Is Something Wrong With Me?</span><hr size=1> I have some good news and some bad news. The good news is it's her. The bad news is it's you too.<br>
<br>
When I was your age (god, I swore I would never start saying that!), I found that the women (in retrospect, they weren't women at all, they were girls) around me couldn't concentrate on ANYTHING for more than a couple of weeks at a time. That was fine though, because neither could I.<br>
<br>
Apparently, this is not the case for you.<br>
<br>
All I can say is, things will improve. Until then, you have to be aware of the fact that most 19 year old girls don't know what the hell they want (no offense intended, most 19 year old boys don't either). <p>Thedosius Dreamtwister<br>
