Maybe you are trying to get too serious too fast and they are freaked out.  I know I dated a guy and like a month after I met him, these talks started coming up about how he wanted to marry me.  I put an end to that really fast, I was 16 and a serious relationship was the last thing on my mind.  I am still friends with Nate and he did end up getting married to one of my friends 3 months after meeting her. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   That was fine for them but not what I wanted.  Anyway, back to the point.<br>
The whole you are a really nice guy, its not you its me line is a classic.  And it is partly you otherwise they wouldn't be saying it.  You sound kind of shy.  I am not sure how chatty you are but I know I hated trying to carry the conversation on my own, it was the one thing that really used to drive me crazy.  Maybe the whole &quot;talking through your friend&quot; thing wasn't a good idea.  She could have taken that as you being too afraid to talk to her, and that is never a good sign.<br>
I think the problem is with this one and maybe others you just moved too fast.  You are young slow down enjoy it, have some fun, and I know you said you are a logical thinker, but hun love is the least logical thing on this planet.  Just let things happen.  If there were no sparks then no big deal, from the sound of it you didn't have a ton of time invested in this relationship and maybe she was just testing the water, you weren't her type of water.  It happens. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
For some reason something I have never understood about young women, and don't get depressed about this, but some of them just love jerks.  Nice guys usually do finish last, but if you were to talk to a 34 year old divorced woman I bet you she would tell you about the nice guy she let get away and how she wished she could have him back.  There are some girls who go through bad boy phases, I was guilty of that myself.  But after dealing with the bad boy/jackass attitude I realized that was not what I wanted for my life.  Give it time, the older you get the more you will find women will be ready for a serious relationship, you are just really young right now and most girls your age are not thinking about long term relationships.<br>
I think you just haven't found the right one yet, but you will.  Keep the faith and have fun. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
(sorry for the babbling, I need a nap) <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><br>
