<br>
1)  Serious relationship?  You're 19.  You ain't ready.  I grew early too and I realize now that I wasnt ready for a real relationship at that time.  YOu dont even fully know yourself yet (though I'm sure your'e saying to yourself right now that you do.  You don't.)<br>
2)  17??  Ok lets go over a few facts here.  98% of women have, as far as I'm concerned, multiple personality disorders.  They have various personalities fighting for control at all times which is why they dont know what they want on the majority of subjects for any real length of time.  The younger the woman, the more predominant the symptoms of this.  Also, as Aiaka said, many women like jerks.  Women and love are illogical.  They want what they cant hang onto or what is a challenge rather than a good thing very often.  Again, the younger they are the worse this is.  <br>
3)  Stop letting your friends hook you up.  They're probably not as intelligent as you and won't pick the best types of women.  Either find your own women or better yet, stay single till you accomplish the things missing listen in item 1. <br>
4)  If you're looking for a relationship to be logical and make sense, give up dating altogether and stick to rosy palm.  <br>
<br>
Now I understand you're probably like me, a hopeless romantic, dead set on finding that true love.  Newsflash:  you're 19.  Also, true love is rare.  Have a good time, date, meet new people, quit looking for love.  Assume it's not gonna come to you for a while.  It may show up, then it can be a surprise, but the more you look for it the more it will elude you.  <br>
<br>
Life's a bitch.  Shit happens.  Either it breaks you or you break it.  I suggest just working on getting yourself where you want to be socially, emotionally, financially and spiritually.  When and if you get to a point in life where you are truly content with being single and are happy with your life and independent, you will be ready for love.  And...NO MORE 17 YEAR OLDS!<br>
