arth kinda guy. Take that advice! <br>
<br>
As a woman, one who is almost 40 years old, I can look back on my life, and I can say, &quot;I've done that!&quot; There are very few things that I've lacked in my life. The reason being, I have a list, (ok, I KNOW that sounds corny, but still... ) on my list is everything I want to do. I call it my LIFE LIST. Everything I want to do/accomplish/see/feel/etc in my life is on that list. There are still several things to be checked off, but for the most part, I've done alot of the things I wanted to accomplish in my life. I have 4 great kids, I've loved with all my heart and soul, and I've been loved in return, those are the things that are pretty rare these days. And while we ALL want to know love, true love, it's a rare commodity in today's world. The only advice I can offer you, is to stop lookin' for it. Be open to it, and when it's meant to be yours, it will find YOU.<br>
<br>
In the meantime.... enjoy life. And don't let the lil things get ya down.... <br>
<br>
And FFS NO more 17 yr olds!!! They have problems deciding day to day whether to wear the blue blouse, or the red one to school, they absolutely have NO CLUE what they want in a life mate!!  <p>&quot;Rational thinking is overrated&quot;<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><br>
