<br>
When I read this, it reminded me how lucky I was to find Hang the way that I did.  We were not friends first.  We met in a very chance circumstance.  <br>
<br>
He was in a Fraternity, I was in a sorority.  His Fraternity held a party called 'strangers in the night' where the brothers had to invite a date for someone else.  I was invited for another brother who I did not get along with at all once I got there (I had never met the person I was asked for so for me the only compelling reason to go was that I had friends who were going to be there).  <br>
<br>
Hang was working that evening, and was not going to go to the party, so no one invited him a date.  He knew my friends from his dorm and he came over and chatted with us (we were hiding from my date in the kitchen).  The two of us enjoyed each other's company so much that I ended up staying past the last shuttle bus to my area of campus.  He walked my home in a blizzard over a mile in the snow, and we talked the entire way.  <br>
<br>
I felt like I had known him my whole life.  I would say that the biggest thing that attracted him to me was that we have very similar morals and very similar views on life (when it comes to the important stuff that is).  He got stuck in my apartment for three days due to the snow.  Luckily my 4 other roommates liked him too, and he was a complete gentleman.  He also will say that the fact that I did not sleep with him is why he called me back after being actually dug out three days later (little note for the other ladies, the better men, the ones that you want to be with long term, do not appreciate woman who do not appear to respect themselves.)<br>
<br>
I told my sister in law two weeks later that I had most likely found the man I would marry.  This is entirely different from the way that I was in the other long term relationships that I was in.  I had dated other men for very long periods of time, and even while I was in the relationships, I knew that they were not leading towards marriage.  <br>
<br>
Another the thing that I will say is that if Hangetsu and I were not married and lovers, we would have been friends.  We LIKE each other as well as love each other.  I still enjoy talking to him and being around him.  He makes me laugh, and he makes me feel lucky every day.<br>
<br>
So I guess my point is, that while we may not have met and become friends before we became lovers, the reason that almost 10 years later we are still happy is because we are friends.  Without that aspect there are times in every relationship that you want to throw in the towel.  Times get tough no matter how happy you are, but if the friendship is true, there is no way that you won't work through those times, and come out the other side happier and stronger.  The friendship (and communication which goes WITH a true friendship) is what you should be cultivating.  And quite honestly if you cultivate friendships and they do not developed into relationships, it is not a wasted effort.  You have a new friend, and if it is a true friendship, it was worth the time you invested anyway.<br>
<br>
Oh, and on a side-ish note: keep to the not drinking too much and staying away from drugs.  I didn't do drugs, I still don't regret it.  I did drink heavily and there are things that I regret due to that, which would have been different if I had been only a moderate drinker.  Have fun and enjoy yourself, you don't need alcohol or drugs to do it, and it sounds like you are the type of person who already knows that. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://mywebpages.comcast.net/Barnes101/wintersbane.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub228.ezboard.com/fxevserverboardsfrm6.showMessageRange?topicID=815.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a><a href=http://pub228.ezboard.com/fxevserverboardsfrm6.showMessageRange?topicID=815.topic&start=41&stop=60>3</a><a href=http://pub228.ezboard.com/fxevserverboardsfrm6.showMessageRange?topicID=815.topic&start=61&stop=80>4</a><a href=http://pub228.ezboard.com/fxevserverboardsfrm6.showMessageRange?topicID=815.topic&start=81&stop=97>5</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub228.ezboard.com/fxevserverboardsfrm6.showPrevMessage?topicID=815.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub228.ezboard.com/fxevserverboardsfrm6.showNextMessage?topicID=815.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub228.ezboard.com/fxevserverboardsfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=815.topic&index=20><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/traditional/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub228.ezboard.com/fxevserverboardsfrm6.emailToFriend?topicID=815.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub228.ezboard.com/fxevserve